rComments: Very kind professor. Her logic of giving the lectures is clear. Also she always prepare biscuits for the students who take the class at night. She answer our questions with patience. Only problem is her pronunciation. Chinese students can easily understand but the other student may not.

Good person however not so good prof. Doesn't know how to explain anything asked in class so if you ask a question you will definitely be left confused. Has good examples however lack of clarity on her part makes it much harder to do well. Spends more time on easier and old concepts but spends less time on newer and harder concepts.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I would definitely not take this prof again. She has been my prof for another course & I thought I would have to give her another chance but I fully regret it. Her lecture slides were a little bit useful but her explanations were sometimes confusing and hard to follow as well & also the term tests were always different from what was taught in class
Her lectures are very detailed and makes the course easier o understand.
She makes you understand some very challenging concepts

I do not recommend this prof to anyone. Lectures are fast paced with non to little time to ask questions. The prof teaches as if you know everything and does not explain throughly. If you do ask questions the answers are usually no help and confuse you more.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lecture heavy', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: I will never take this prof again, and I wish I never did. In first year proofs, she rushes through everything so quickly as if she is teaching to some people that already passed the course. She is really smart, but she cannot teach to save her life. Even if you ask questions she is NO help at all, you are honestly better off teaching yourself.

Professor Wang is a very nice person; however, I don't think she is a very good professor. There was lots of important information left out of our lectures that showed up on our exam and on some of the quizzes. Her lectures did not prepare us for the course assessments. I talked to people with other profs, and they were getting much more info.
